  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.5.4">
<l>pēyttāyai mulaiyuṇṭa piḷḷai taṉṉaip piṇaimaruppil karuṅkaḷiṟṟaip piṇaimāṉ ṉōkkiṉ</l>
<l>āyttāyar tayirveṇṇe yamarnta kōvai yantaṇarta mamutattaik kuravai muṉṉē</l>
<l>kōttāṉaik kuṭamāṭu kūttaṉ ṟaṉṉaik kōkulaṅkaḷ taḷarāmal kuṉṟa mēntik</l>
<l>kāttāṉai yemmāṉaik kaṇṭu koṇṭēṉ kaṭipoḻilcūḻ kaṭalmallait talaca yaṉattē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The child who ate [from] the breast of the demon mother,</l>
<l rend="indent">the black bull elephant with twin tusks,</l>
<l>The king who craved the curds and ghee of the herder ladies</l>
<l rend="indent">with doe[-like] eyes, nectar of the brahmins,</l>
<l>He who long ago locked [hands] in the kuravai [dance],</l>
<l rend="indent">the performer who danced with pots,</l>
<l>The guardian who bore a hill so the herders would not suffer, our lord,</l>
<l>I saw for myself in Talacayaṉam encircled by fragrant gardens at Mallai by the sea.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
